import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import coint
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for a pair of stocks from Yahoo Finance
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for WMT...")
wmt_data = yf.download("WMT", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for TGT...")
tgt_data = yf.download("TGT", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract the 'Close' column
wmt_prices = wmt_data["Close"].dropna()
tgt_prices = tgt_data["Close"].dropna()
print("WMT Prices Head:\n", wmt_prices.head())
print("TGT Prices Head:\n", tgt_prices.head())

# Step 2: Perform cointegration test
score, p_value, _ = coint(wmt_prices, tgt_prices)
print(f"Cointegration test p-value: {p_value}")

# Interpret the p-value
if p_value < 0.05:
    print("WMT and TGT are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("WMT and TGT are not cointegrated.")

# Step 3: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_prices, label="WMT Prices", color="blue")
plt.plot(tgt_prices.index, tgt_prices, label="TGT Prices", color="green")
plt.title("Stock Prices")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for WMT and TGT from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for WMT...")
wmt_data = yf.download("WMT", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for TGT...")
tgt_data = yf.download("TGT", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
wmt_prices = wmt_data["Close"].dropna()
tgt_prices = tgt_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([wmt_prices, tgt_prices], axis=1).dropna()
wmt_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
tgt_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

wmt_rw = random_walk_simulation(wmt_prices.iloc[0], len(wmt_prices), scale=5)
tgt_rw = random_walk_simulation(tgt_prices.iloc[0], len(tgt_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

wmt_returns = wmt_prices.pct_change().dropna()
tgt_returns = tgt_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(wmt_prices, "WMT Prices")
unit_root_test(tgt_prices, "TGT Prices")
unit_root_test(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")
unit_root_test(tgt_returns, "TGT Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

wmt_arma = fit_arma(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")
tgt_arma = fit_arma(tgt_returns, "TGT Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(wmt_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of WMT ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(wmt_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of WMT ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(tgt_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of TGT ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(tgt_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of TGT ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between WMT and TGT Prices:")
coint_result = coint(wmt_prices, tgt_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - WMT and TGT prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - WMT and TGT prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_prices, label="WMT Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_rw, label="WMT Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(tgt_prices.index, tgt_prices, label="TGT Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(tgt_prices.index, tgt_rw, label="TGT Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index, wmt_returns, label="WMT Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(tgt_returns.index, tgt_returns, label="TGT Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
wmt_forecast = wmt_arma.forecast(steps=30)
tgt_forecast = tgt_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=wmt_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index[-30:], wmt_returns[-30:], label="WMT Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, wmt_forecast, label="WMT ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(tgt_returns.index[-30:], tgt_returns[-30:], label="TGT Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, tgt_forecast, label="TGT ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for KO and PEP from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for KO...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for PEP...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
ko_prices = ko_data["Close"].dropna()
pep_prices = pep_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([ko_prices, pep_prices], axis=1).dropna()
ko_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
pep_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

ko_rw = random_walk_simulation(ko_prices.iloc[0], len(ko_prices), scale=5)
pep_rw = random_walk_simulation(pep_prices.iloc[0], len(pep_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

ko_returns = ko_prices.pct_change().dropna()
pep_returns = pep_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(ko_prices, "KO Prices")
unit_root_test(pep_prices, "PEP Prices")
unit_root_test(ko_returns, "KO Returns")
unit_root_test(pep_returns, "PEP Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

ko_arma = fit_arma(ko_returns, "KO Returns")
pep_arma = fit_arma(pep_returns, "PEP Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of KO ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of KO ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of PEP ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of PEP ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between KO and PEP Prices:")
coint_result = coint(ko_prices, pep_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - KO and PEP prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - KO and PEP prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="KO Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_rw, label="KO Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="PEP Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_rw, label="PEP Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(ko_returns.index, ko_returns, label="KO Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_returns.index, pep_returns, label="PEP Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
ko_forecast = ko_arma.forecast(steps=30)
pep_forecast = pep_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=ko_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(ko_returns.index[-30:], ko_returns[-30:], label="KO Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ko_forecast, label="KO ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pep_returns.index[-30:], pep_returns[-30:], label="PEP Actual Returns", color="green")

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import coint
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for KO and PEP from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for KO...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for PEP...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)

ko_prices = ko_data["Close"].dropna()
pep_prices = pep_data["Close"].dropna()
print("KO Prices Head:\n", ko_prices.head())
print("PEP Prices Head:\n", pep_prices.head())

# Step 2: Perform cointegration test
score, p_value, _ = coint(ko_prices, pep_prices)
print(f"Cointegration test p-value: {p_value}")

# Interpret the p-value
if p_value < 0.05:
    print("KO and PEP are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("KO and PEP are not cointegrated.")

# Step 3: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="KO Prices", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="PEP Prices", color="green")
plt.title("Stock Prices")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for XOM and CVX from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for XOM...")
xom_data = yf.download("XOM", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for CVX...")
cvx_data = yf.download("CVX", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
xom_prices = xom_data["Close"].dropna()
cvx_prices = cvx_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([xom_prices, cvx_prices], axis=1).dropna()
xom_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
cvx_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

xom_rw = random_walk_simulation(xom_prices.iloc[0], len(xom_prices), scale=5)
cvx_rw = random_walk_simulation(cvx_prices.iloc[0], len(cvx_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

xom_returns = xom_prices.pct_change().dropna()
cvx_returns = cvx_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(xom_prices, "XOM Prices")
unit_root_test(cvx_prices, "CVX Prices")
unit_root_test(xom_returns, "XOM Returns")
unit_root_test(cvx_returns, "CVX Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

xom_arma = fit_arma(xom_returns, "XOM Returns")
cvx_arma = fit_arma(cvx_returns, "CVX Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(xom_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of XOM ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(xom_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of XOM ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(cvx_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of CVX ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(cvx_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of CVX ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between XOM and CVX Prices:")
coint_result = coint(xom_prices, cvx_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - XOM and CVX prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - XOM and CVX prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(xom_prices.index, xom_prices, label="XOM Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(xom_prices.index, xom_rw, label="XOM Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(cvx_prices.index, cvx_prices, label="CVX Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(cvx_prices.index, cvx_rw, label="CVX Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(xom_returns.index, xom_returns, label="XOM Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(cvx_returns.index, cvx_returns, label="CVX Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
xom_forecast = xom_arma.forecast(steps=30)
cvx_forecast = cvx_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=xom_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(xom_returns.index[-30:], xom_returns[-30:], label="XOM Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, xom_forecast, label="XOM ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")

plt.plot(forecast_index, cvx_forecast, label="CVX ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
